Scalability

Our users may operate with limited information at the time of provisioning their namespaces, resulting in best-effort provisioning estimates. Further, evolving use-cases may introduce new throughput requirements over time. Hereâ€™s how we manage this:

Horizontal scaling : TimeSeries server instances can auto-scale up and down as per attached scaling policies to meet the traffic demand. The storage server capacity can be recomputed to accommodate changing requirements using our capacity planner.

